{
  "id": "S2R2N216",
  "title": {
    "product_var": "ZPRODTSK",
    "text": "EDIT PRIMARY COMMAND - STATS",
    "version_var": "ZSHRTVER",
    "prefix": "HELP"
  },
  "type": "menu",
  "body": {
    "rows": [
      {
        "type": "command",
        "variable": "ZCMD"
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "Purpose"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "The STATS command will generate statistics (level stamping) when"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "standard numbering is ON."
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "Format"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "STATS [ ON | OFF ]"
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "Remarks"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "When STATS is ON and line numbering is standard (STD), columns 79 and"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "80 contain a level number. Each time SPF/PC starts editing such a file,"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "it finds the highest level number and adds one to it. Unless the number"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "is overwritten by a LEVEL command, it places this new number in the"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "level number field of any record that is changed or inserted. By using"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "this, you can tell which records have been updated and relatively when"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "the update took place."
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
